# PBooks Pro – Commands

## Environments overview

| | **Staging** | **Production** |
|---|-------------|----------------|
| **Git branch** | `staging` | `main` |
| **PostgreSQL DB** | `pBookspro_Staging` | `pbookspro` |
| **Env file** | `.env.staging` | `.env.production` |
| **API port** (same machine) | **3001** | **3000** |
| **Release command** | `npm run release:staging` | `npm run release:production` |
| **GitHub release type** | Prerelease (manual) | Full release (manual deploy; CI validates on push to `main`) |
| **Installers** | API Server (Staging) + Client (Staging) | API Server + Client |

Both APIs can run on the **same local machine** at different ports.

### One-time env setup

Env files are gitignored. Copy the examples and set your connection strings:

```powershell
copy .env.staging.example .env.staging
copy .env.production.example .env.production
```

**Local PostgreSQL (no password):**

```env
# .env.staging
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:@127.0.0.1:5432/pBookspro_Staging
PORT=3001
GH_TOKEN=ghp_...   # for GitHub prerelease publish

# .env.production
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:@127.0.0.1:5432/pbookspro
PORT=3000
GH_TOKEN=ghp_...   # for GitHub full release publish
```

**Initial migrations (once per database):**

```powershell
npm run db:migrate:staging
npm run db:migrate:production
```

